- Total value of raw materials imported in the previous year: 330.44 lakhs
- Value of raw materials imported in the current year: 1596.85 lakhs

We can calculate the percentage of raw material imported in the previous year using the following formula:

Percentage = (Value of raw material imported in previous year / Value of raw material imported in current year) x 100

Plugging in the values, we get:

Percentage = (330.44 / 1596.85) x 100 â‰ˆ 20.77%

This means that the percentage of raw material imported in the previous year is approximately 20.77%.
